      "writtenOn": "2019-08-14T14:59:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, this is just me trying to match the existing bilerp_clamp_8888 to start.  It may make sense to try fixed point here, but I think I started that way last time and ended up with precision trouble until I switched up to 32-bit.\n\nWe\u0027ll also need to make sure we support negative weights and handle the accumulation more carefully in sampler() if we want it to support bicubic.  It\u0027s a total mess as-is.\n\nI guess we can accumulate in signed 16-bit, and if that doesn\u0027t look good enough, in 32-bit int or float?",
      "parentUuid": "61f59686_7ab5821c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4040,
        "startChar": 19,
        "endLine": 4040,
        "endChar": 20
